==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intimidation
<hw>In*tim`i*da"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>intimidation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of making timid or fearful
or of deterring by threats; the state of being intimidated; <as>as, the
voters were kept from the polls by <ex>intimidation</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The king carried his measures in Parliament by
<qex>intimidation</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Paley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intimidatory</ent>⟦br⟧
